アーカイブを聴きながら勉強している者です。このコメントが誰かに読まれることは無いかも知れませんが思いを書かなくてはと思い、このコメントを打っています。
BGMがオルゴールに変わってるしあちゃんが嬉しそうに、楽しそうに話しているのを聞いて涙が溢れてきました。今はもう潤羽るしあとしてこの声は聴けないけど、みなさんの心の中に残っていると思います。このチャンネルが残っている限り聴きに来れるのが唯一の救いです。ありがとうございます。
起きてしまったことはもうどうしようもないけど、僕を含め多くの人がるしあちゃんの事が大好きです。
今まで潤羽るしあをありがとう。

author: 海神〈わだつみ〉
text:
拝啓　るしあさん

私は貴方の姿に、声に、言葉にたくさん助けられてきました。
配信をリアルタイムで見ることは出来なかった。
メンバーシップに入ることも出来なかった。
でも、ずっと応援していました。
今でも応援しています。
この先も応援しています。
チャンネルは消えてしまうけど「るしあ」という存在は私の記憶に、心に残り続けます。
初配信から今までの配信で貴方が頑張ってきた事は多くの人の心にも残ります。
今は辛いこと、悲しいこと多くあると思います。
今は前を向けないかもしれません。
泣いても良いです。
怒っても良いです。
ゆっくり休んで下さい。
そしていつかまた、優しい、楽しい笑顔を取り戻して下さい。

まだ貴方にメッセージが届くか分からないけど、、、
本当に貴方のことを好きです。
いつか貴方と再び何処かで出会える日を夢見ています。
本当にありがとうございました。
そしてお疲れ様でした。

author: zeijuro
text: The reason why I chose this video for this message to be posted in is because, this is the most memorable stream of Rushia, for me. I don't even care anymore if my English is broken. At first I was planning to translate this message into japanese, but I wanted to type a message that will not leave me anymore regrets. RUSHIA, THANK YOU. Thank you for everything you have done for us, for me. When times were hard for me, listening to this ASMR video helps me calm myself. It's like magic. My Japanese is not that good, but I heard sentences, words, phrases, and compliments that I really wanted someone to tell me. It's like you really know what to say, despite us not knowing each other. I think I am being a creep just for saying this, but I don't care anymore. I don't want to  have anymore regrets. I don't want to half-ass anything anymore. I really want to express my deepest gratitude for you. When I first heard about your channel, I thought it was childish for someone to simp to a 2d girl. But little did I know that I will dive really deep into this rabbit hole. But I do not have regrets. Because of Vtubers, I started to binge watch a lot of anime series. After that, I discovered different Vtubers. Vtubers truly are a blessing for people like me, who really love 2d girls. Listening or watching streams of different Vtubers really make my day. They always put a smile on my face. But, yours has some magic in it. Everytime I visit your streams, my anxieties, worries, and other problems disappear. I just want to get this feeling off my chest. This, heavy, crushing, weight. You made a lot of people happy, people like me. Thera are a lot of people who really appreciates your streams. I really, really am grateful that I went in this channel, this family perhaps. Watching your streams with different people really is a fun experience. Hearing your screams, and jokes never fail to make us smile and laugh. Watching clips of you with your friends in Hololive with my friends will always be a memory I will cherish. The smiles you put on our faces. I will cherish it all. I will NEVER forget you and I will NEVER disown this memory. Everyone will remember you. You made a huge impact in this community. I may never hear from you again, at least in this channel, but always know that I WILL ALWAYS support you, I WILL ALWAYS remember you and I WILL ALWAYS respect you. I think I said all that is need to be said. I still don't know if I will calm down after writing this message. Thank you RUSHIA. Thank you for being a VTuber. Thank you for being a blessing that came to my life. I sincerely thank you.

author: AmAzing Cager
text:
52:00ここ聞いて泣いたから自分語りするけど許して
俺バスケやっててそこそこ強いチーム入っててプロ目指して本気で練習してそれ以外なんもなくて、最近伸び悩んでてもうやめた方がいいんかなとも思ってる。
最近リフレッシュのためにパソコン買おうと思ってるんだけど、それはバスケから逃げてんじゃねえかって自分を肯定できなかったり別にバスケでプロになるのとかそのために練習すんのって幸せなのかなって思ったり、でも今更やめれないしなとか思ったりして。
もう色々キツくて、周りで頼れる人もいなくて、辛い。
ありがとう、るしあちゃん。大好き。

author: ゆまるーー
text:
僕もフルコンタクト空手をやってたんですけど、そういった事よくありましたよ。伸びなくなった時は、自分が今までやってきたことをもう一度見直せば良いんです。そんなの既に何度もやってるしと思うかも知れませんが、一度やってきたことが試合で使えなければ覚えた意味がないですよね？何度もするんです。僕は1つの事だけに力を注ぎたかったので、蹴りの面ではローキックばかり練習してきました。それでちゃんと勝てた試合もあります。簡単に言ってしまいますがバスケでも同じような感覚だと思います。上では覚えた事をもう一度見直すと言いましたが、それが無理なら全部が全部しようとするんじゃなくて、自分が一番得意な事だけを中心にやってみるのも良いと思います。
強くなりたいと言う一心があるなら必ず努力は報われますよ。
長文失礼しました。
バスケ頑張って下さいね。

author: AmAzing Cager
text:
@ゆまるーー  アドバイスありがとうございます！
なんかすごい説得力あります
この期間に一度基礎をやり直してみます
プロになってみせます
バスケ頑張ります！

If you think about it, watching a Rushia ASMR stream requires a lot of trust. If she just started going full necromancer mode your eardrums will explode into a pile of blood on the spot. 

FYI, whispering really hurts your voice, so kudos to her for doing it for 3 hours straight. Just a small reminder, the actual stream was 1h, and she pulled another 2 hours (bless me, I was in my bed sleeping at that time) BUT she did mention that her throat is made of steel and screaming doesn’t affect her, so I doubt that will be a problem. 

She also cured my bloody insomnia this week. It was torturous. At least it’s finally gone now.

author: Probing Uranus
text: @Oh yeah yeah Im asian  Try to whisper for a long time while reading a book and you'll see your throat will start hurting eventually. It puts more of strain on the voice than normal speak. It's why when you have a soar throat, it's better to speak as little as possible since whispering can hurt it even more. It's better to go for soft speak in such situations. I love listening to soft-spoken ASMR too. Rushia's ASMR was a mix of soft speech and whispering. That's why she could do it for so long.

author: Why AlwaysMe
text: @Probing Uranus  i used to whisper for 1 hour straight because me and my friends were playing hide and seek for 2 hours. i dont remember hurting my voice. i think you're just whispering wrongly or your have weak throat

author: Probing Uranus
text: @Why AlwaysMe  I don't know the circumstances or if you did whisper for 1 hour without breaks but it is believed that whispering puts more strain on your voice. Just google "does whispering hurt your voice" and you will find a bunch of articles that confirm this. Though there are recent researchs that say not all feel discomfort while whispering but for majority it puts more strain on the voice. It might be that you're in the group that has no trouble whispering. Each person's vocal chords is different so this result isn't that far fetched.
